1 L.D. 1535
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 ENERGY, UTILITIES AND TECHNOLOGY
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 619, L.D. 1535, “An Act to Reduce
10 Illegal Cannabis Operations by Requiring Permits for High Electrical Usage”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Direct the Public Utilities Commission to Facilitate Stakeholder
13 Discussions Related to High Electrical Usage'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Stakeholder discussion. Resolved: That the Public Utilities Commission
16 shall facilitate at least one meeting among stakeholders to discuss the subject matter of L.D.
17 1535, An Act to Reduce Illegal Cannabis Operations by Requiring Permits for High
18 Electrical Usage, as introduced in the First Special Session of the 132nd Legislature. The
19 stakeholders must include representatives from the following organizations:
20 1. Consumer-owned and investor-owned transmission and distribution utilities;
21 2. The Maine Sheriffs' Association;
22 3. The Maine State Police;
23 4. The Maine Municipal Association;
24 5. The Office of the State Fire Marshal; and
25 6. The Maine Fire Chiefs' Association.
26 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, by January 15, 2026, the Public Utilities
27 Commission shall provide a report summarizing the stakeholder discussions under section
28 1, including any recommendations, to the Joint Standing Committee on Energy, Utilities
29 and Technology. The committee may report out a bill relating to the report to the Second
30 Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
