COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 619, L.D. 1535
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. It requires the Public Utilities
33 Commission to facilitate at least one discussion among stakeholders regarding the subject
44 matter of L.D. 1535, An Act to Reduce Illegal Cannabis Operations by Requiring Permits
55 for High Electrical Usage, as introduced in the First Special Session of the 132nd
66 Legislature. By January 15, 2026, the commission must provide a report summarizing the
77 discussions, including any recommendations, to the Joint Standing Committee on Energy,
88 Utilities and Technology.
99 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1100 (See attached)
